President Donald J. Trump met with General Zulkifeli bin Muhammad Zin, Director General of the Malaysian National Security Council, to express gratitude for Malaysia's assistance in recovering fallen US sailors. The President also mentioned his anticipation of welcoming Malaysian Prime Minister Najib Abdul Razak to the White House in September. General Zulkifeli was in Washington, D.C. to meet with Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs LTG H.R. McMaster. The two officials discussed ways to strengthen bilateral ties, particularly in trade, investment, defense, and security cooperation. The aim is to address shared challenges and promote regional peace and stability, including the fight against ISIS and other extremist networks.